Package: CELTYC
Title: Cell type specific clustering
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2024-3-25
Author: Qi Luo, Andrew E. Teschendorff <andrew@sinh.ac.cn>
Maintainer: Qi Luo, Andrew E. Teschendorff <andrew@sinh.ac.cn>
Description: CELTYC is an R package that implements cell type specific
    clustering pipeline given a DNA methylation data matrix. It includes
    the process of estimating cell type fractions within a tissue type,
    identifying disease-associated DMCs altered in specific cell types,
    and unsupervised clustering with the identified DMCTs for different
    cell types.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports: ConsensusClusterPlus, EpiDISH, parallel, r.jive, stats
Suggests: BiocStyle, ComplexHeatmap, EpiSCORE, knitr, rmarkdown,
        SuperExactTest, survival
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
NeedsCompilation: no
Packaged: 2024-10-15 10:06:41 UTC; luoqi
